This paper deals with space-efficient algorithms for distance oracles, distance labeling, and labeled routing, which are all topics in the field of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization, which are relevant to cs.DM and cs.CG. The use of approximation algorithms and stretch trade-offs suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and simulation and modeling (cs.SI).
